<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-02-12T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-02-12T16:00:00-05:00" n="637" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d637">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">704.5483/18: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Howell</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-02-12T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February 12,
                                        1926—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>2. Your written despatch 745, January 18. You may inform British High
                            Commissioner that if requested by the Swiss Government the Department
                            would be pleased to instruct its representatives in Egypt to relinquish
                            the representation of such Swiss interests in that country as are at
                            present under their protection.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
